    {"day": 42, "title": "Perfect Love", "scripture": "1 John 4:18", "verse_text": "There is no fear in love; but perfect love casteth out fear: because fear hath torment. He that feareth is not made perfect in love.", "reflection": "God's perfect love drives out all fear. In His love, we find freedom from fear.", "prayer": "Father, let Your perfect love cast out every fear in my heart."},
    {"day": 43, "title": "Pressing Forward", "scripture": "Philippians 3:13-14", "verse_text": "Brethren, I count not myself to have apprehended: but this one thing I do, forgetting those things which are behind, and reaching forth unto those things which are before, I press toward the mark for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.", "reflection": "We must forget the past and press forward toward God's calling on our lives.", "prayer": "Lord, help me forget the past and press toward the prize of Your calling."},
