        {"scripture": "Micah 6:8", "verse_text": "He hath shewed thee, O man, what is good; and what doth the LORD require of thee, but to do justly, and to love mercy, and to walk humbly with thy God?", "title": "What God Requires", "reflection": "God requires justice, mercy, and humble walking with Him.", "prayer": "Lord, help me do justice, love mercy, and walk humbly with You."},
        {"scripture": "Matthew 5:16", "verse_text": "Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father which is in heaven.", "title": "Shining Light", "reflection": "Our good works should shine as a light, bringing glory to God.", "prayer": "Lord, let my light shine for Your glory today."},
