        {"scripture": "John 16:33", "verse_text": "These things I have spoken unto you, that in me ye might have peace. In the world ye shall have tribulation: but be of good cheer; I have overcome the world.", "title": "Overcoming Peace", "reflection": "In Christ we have peace despite tribulation because He has overcome the world.", "prayer": "Jesus, thank You for Your peace and victory over the world."},
        {"scripture": "Acts 1:8", "verse_text": "But ye shall receive power, after that the Holy Ghost is come upon you: and ye shall be witnesses unto me both in Jerusalem, and in all Judaea, and in Samaria, and unto the uttermost part of the earth.", "title": "Power to Witness", "reflection": "The Holy Spirit gives us power to be witnesses for Christ everywhere.", "prayer": "Holy Spirit, empower me to be a witness for Jesus today."},
        {"scripture": "Romans 8:1", "verse_text": "There is therefore now no condemnation to them which are in Christ Jesus, who walk not after the flesh, but after the Spirit.", "title": "No Condemnation", "reflection": "In Christ, there is no condemnation - complete freedom from guilt.", "prayer": "Thank You, Jesus, that there is no condemnation for me in You."},
        {"scripture": "Romans 8:28", "verse_text": "And we know that all things work together for good to them that love God, to them who are the called according to his purpose.", "title": "All Things for Good", "reflection": "God works all things together for the good of those who love Him.", "prayer": "Lord, I trust that You are working all things for my good."},
        {"scripture": "1 Corinthians 10:13", "verse_text": "There hath no temptation taken you but such as is common to man: but God is faithful, who will not suffer you to be tempted above that ye are able; but will with the temptation also make a way to escape, that ye may be able to bear it.", "title": "Way of Escape", "reflection": "God always provides a way out of temptation. He is faithful.", "prayer": "Lord, show me Your way of escape when temptation comes."},
        {"scripture": "1 Corinthians 13:4-5", "verse_text": "Charity suffereth long, and is kind; charity envieth not; charity vaunteth not itself, is not puffed up, Doth not behave itself unseemly, seeketh not her own, is not easily provoked, thinketh no evil.", "title": "Love's Character", "reflection": "True love is patient, kind, humble, and selfless.", "prayer": "Lord, fill me with Your patient, kind, selfless love."},
